                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-238-victim1378 t18280221-238-viclabel1267"></join>.</p>
               <p>MARY VARRELL. I live in <placeName id="t18280221-238-crimeloc1268">Norton-street, Portland-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-238-crimeloc1268" type="placeName" value="Norton-street, Portland-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-238-crimeloc1268" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-238-off1265 t18280221-238-crimeloc1268"></join>. I lost a shawl out of my box, between six and seven o'clock in the morning of the 6th of February; the prisoner lodged in the same apartment, and was to go away that morning: she slept in the same bed with me. My box was not locked; I am quite sure it was there - she had nothing in the room; she had slept there for a month - her mother lived in Middlesex-buildings. I got up about eight o'clock and went to my box to get some money; I had 10s. 7 1/2d. there; it was gone: the landlady, who slept in the same room, rose at five o'clock. I saw the shawl at the pawnbroker's on the Saturday evening following - I never had lent it to her; I only went there on the previous Saturday.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182802210127"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-238-person1379">
                  HENRY 
                  ROW
               <interp inst="t18280221-238-person1379" type="surname" value="ROW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-238-person1379" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-238-person1379" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. Morris, pawnbroker, High-street, Mary-le-bone. I took this shawl in of the prisoner - I had seen her before; it was on the 6th of February - I advanced 5s. on it in the name of Maria Wheatley, of William-street, by which name we had done business with her.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-238-person1380">
                  HENRY 
                  STOWELL
               <interp inst="t18280221-238-person1380" type="surname" value="STOWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-238-person1380" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-238-person1380" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer of High-street, Mary-le-bone. The prisoner came to the office to swear to the loss of a duplicate; Mary Varrell had told me of the loss of her shawl - the prisoner was not sworn, but I took her into custody.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I took the shawl on the Wednesday morning, when I left - I took it to buy a pair of shoes to go to my uncle's; and if I had got the shoes, and gone there, I should have had money, and returned it that very evening.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280221-238-verdict1269" type="verdictDescription">
